parameters.description: : Available Exhaustible View Criteria to use for retrieving exhaustible resources.
parameters.name: _criteria

operations.notes:
The Get Available Exhaustible Resources end point provides a list of available exhaustible resources for a length of time as described by the passed in Criteria value. Alternatively, it can provide the status of a current resource for the given time period if the resource is identified in the Criteria parameter.

This operation requires a Available Exhaustible View Criteria value.

This operation returns a Exhaustible View Wrapper with the following fields:

Name Data Type Description
views List of Exhaustible View values View of exhaustible resources matching the search criteria.
hasAdditional Boolean value Indicates in paginated calls if there are additional views which can be requested.
nextStartRow Integer value Index of next row at which to start request for additional values.
unavailabilityCode Integer value Sub code of type Availability Exception which gives the reason for an empty availability list being returned.

Note: If no availabilities are returned, the returned object may include an unavailability code value indicating the reason for the empty list. This code matches the sub error codes defined for the Availability Exception type.

responseMessages.message:
Unauthorized User

If the User does not have permissions to request available exhaustible resources, or the User Authentication Token is invalid, one of the following exceptions are returned:

  • Authentication Exception if the requestor cannot be authenticated using the provided Authentication token.
  • Authorization Exception if the requestor identified by the Authorization token is not authorized to perform this action.

Invalid Search Criteria

If the search criteria provided is somehow invalid, the following exception is returned:

  • Business Exception if the search criteria is invalid.

Unrecoverable Error

A System Exception is returned if the operation has caused an unrecoverable state.

parameters.description: Service View Criteria object to determine which services to query for availability
parameters.name: _criteria

operations.notes:
Get those services which are available and match the given service criteria for the given time period.

This operation requires a Available Service View Criteria value.

This operation returns a Availability Service View Wrapper with the following fields:

Name Data Type Description
views List of Service View values View of service resources matching the search criteria.
hasAdditional Boolean value Indicates in paginated calls if there are additional views which can be requested.
nextStartRow Integer value Index of next row at which to start request for additional values.

responseMessages.message:
Unauthorized User

If the User does not have permissions to request available service resources or the User Authentication Token is invalid, one of the following exceptions are returned:

  • Authentication Exception if the requestor cannot be authenticated using the provided Authentication token.
  • Authorization Exception if the requestor identified by the Authorization token is not authorized to perform this action.

Invalid Search Criteria

If the search criteria provided is somehow invalid, the following exception is returned:

  • Business Exception if the search criteria is invalid.

Unrecoverable Error

A System Exception is returned if the operation has caused an unrecoverable state.

AuthenticationException - if the requestor cannot authenticatedAuthorizationException - if the requestor is not authorized to perform this actionBusinessException - if there are business rule violationsSystemException - if an unrecoverable error occurs

operations.notes:
This operation returns a list of times and dates for which the resources (or Assets) which is identified in the request is not available or requested by another user. The range of dates for which the unavailability is checked is also determined by the posted argument for this operation.

NOTE: This operation can only be used for Exhaustible resources, which include Workspaces and Non-workspace rooms.

This operation requires a Unavailable Block Request argument value.

This operation returns a Unavailable Block Response value.

responseMessages.message:
Unauthorized User

If the User does not have permissions to request available resources or the User Authentication Token is invalid, one of the following exceptions are returned:

  • Authentication Exception if the requestor cannot be authenticated using the provided Authentication token.
  • Authorization Exception if the requestor identified by the Authorization token is not authorized to perform this action.

Resource Not Found

If the search criteria includes the SYSID of a Resource which does not exist in the system, the following exception is returned:

  • Not Found Exception if the identified Resource cannot be found.

Unrecoverable Error

A System Exception is returned if the operation has caused an unrecoverable state.
